        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="1154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660F.6231/8–2145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-23T19:00:00-04:00">August 23, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. Dept would appreciate your views as to post Potsdam status of CRAB and its
                    various subcommittees. Is there any evident inclination to de-emphasize the role
                    of these bodies in favor of anticipated quadripartite organization or do they
                    remain fully operative? In particular, are the proposed foreign trade
                    transactions (urtel 335, Aug 21) to be engaged in under the authority and
                    supervision of CRAB or are these transactions envisaged as barter deals between
                    the US zone and the countries concerned requiring policy determination only on
                    the US side?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
